config.prompt:
Watch this short security camera clip and produce a structured activity log entry. Focus on what's actually happening, not just what's visible — the goal is a searchable record an operator can scan months later.

Respond with ONLY a JSON object - no prose, no code fence - with exactly three keys:
  "subject_type": one of "person", "vehicle", "animal", "object", or "none". When multiple are present, pick the most prominent. Use "none" if the clip is empty / scenery only.
  "activity":     a 1-4 word verb phrase describing what the subject is doing (e.g. "walking past", "loading truck", "climbing fence", "investigating door", "driving by"). Use "present" if just standing still. Use "none" if subject_type is "none".
  "summary":      one sentence describing the event for the activity log, max 180 characters. Lead with the subject and what it did. No filler like "this video shows" - just the facts.

Do not invent details that aren't visible. If the clip is unclear or dark, say so in the summary and use "low" confidence wording.

Examples:
  {"subject_type": "person", "activity": "walking past", "summary": "Adult in dark jacket walked east-to-west across the loading dock, no interaction with cargo."}
  {"subject_type": "vehicle", "activity": "backing in", "summary": "White van backed into bay 3 and a driver exited the cab, no visible signage."}
  {"subject_type": "none", "activity": "none", "summary": "Wind-blown debris triggered motion - empty driveway, no person or vehicle present."}
